cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a technique for scene text reading, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of histograms of oriented gradients, which is a common feature descriptor used in object detection and recognition, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
